[Team leader Baek Su Jeong]

2
00:00:27,664 --> 00:00:30,333
[Moon Ga Young]

3
00:00:31,753 --> 00:00:33,073
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

4
00:00:33,073 --> 00:00:35,893
[Choi Hyeon Wook]

5
00:00:35,893 --> 00:00:37,673
[The heir of Yongsung. Is there a new Chaebol director?]

6
00:00:39,763 --> 00:00:41,913
[Im Se Mi]

7
00:00:42,693 --> 00:00:44,632
[Kwak Shi Yang]

8
00:00:55,352 --> 00:00:58,931
My Dearest Nemesis

9
00:00:58,930 --> 00:01:00,450
[This drama is entirely fictional.]

10
00:01:00,450 --> 00:01:02,340
[The characters and settings are fictional.]

11
00:01:02,340 --> 00:01:03,830
[Filming with children took place in a safe environment.]

12
00:01:24,590 --> 00:01:26,620
He's crazy.

13
00:01:42,030 --> 00:01:44,349
Why did he kiss me?

14
00:01:44,349 --> 00:01:46,739
I know he was drunk, but still.

15
00:01:46,739 --> 00:01:49,269
No matter how often I think about it,

16
00:01:49,269 --> 00:01:50,889
There is only one reason.

17
00:01:50,889 --> 00:01:53,439
It's too late to take the dress to the dry cleaners.

18
00:01:53,439 --> 00:01:55,649
You should keep it.

19
00:01:55,649 --> 00:01:57,329
What why?

20
00:01:57,329 --> 00:01:59,379
I don't need it

21
00:01:59,379 --> 00:02:00,629
And it was beautiful.

22
00:02:00,629 --> 00:02:03,579
Because you're the only one who would give me chocolate milk, Mrs. Baek.

23
00:02:03,579 --> 00:02:06,459
Because you're the only one who would give me chocolate milk, Mrs. Baek.

24
00:02:13,709 --> 00:02:15,079
Is...

25
00:02:15,759 --> 00:02:18,079
likes me.

26
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:20,668
If that's the case, then he should just say so.

27
00:02:20,668 --> 00:02:23,608
Why did he scare me with a sudden kiss?

28
00:02:23,608 --> 00:02:26,078
How will he see me from now on?

29
00:02:26,078 --> 00:02:29,088
Good grief. Since when does he like me?

30
00:02:29,088 --> 00:02:31,098
Was it...

31
00:02:31,098 --> 00:02:33,088
from the beginning?

32
00:02:38,698 --> 00:02:40,558
My goodness.

33
00:02:41,108 --> 00:02:43,548
I was awake all night.

34
00:03:04,087 --> 00:03:05,417
Nun...

35
00:03:05,417 --> 00:03:08,607
You're up early.

36
00:03:09,467 --> 00:03:11,937
I couldn't sleep well.

37
00:03:11,937 --> 00:03:13,957
You couldn't sleep?

38
00:03:13,957 --> 00:03:15,687
No.

39
00:03:15,687 --> 00:03:16,767
Just as you expected.

40
00:03:16,767 --> 00:03:19,897
As expected, he was too excited to sleep.

41
00:03:19,897 --> 00:03:23,167
How could he sleep after something like that?

42
00:03:23,167 --> 00:03:25,497
I tend to be picky about where I sleep.

43
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:28,277
An obvious excuse. Fine.

44
00:03:28,277 --> 00:03:31,276
Oh, I see.

45
00:03:31,276 --> 00:03:34,546
You're the one who woke up early.

46
00:03:34,546 --> 00:03:36,926
Didn't you sleep well?

47
00:03:36,926 --> 00:03:38,476
I?

48
00:03:39,036 --> 00:03:41,626
Well, no, I really did sleep well.

49
00:03:41,626 --> 00:03:45,536
I am a morning person, an "early bird" who is always working.

50
00:03:45,536 --> 00:03:47,746
An early bird...

51
00:03:48,826 --> 00:03:50,676
Do you have

52
00:03:53,266 --> 00:03:57,516
Would you happen to fancy joining me for a walk?

53
00:03:58,306 --> 00:04:00,136
Where?

54
00:04:01,806 --> 00:04:04,706
There's a nice spot over there.

55
00:04:04,706 --> 00:04:07,515
Why go to a nice spot?

56
00:04:07,515 --> 00:04:09,205
Will he confess his love to me?

57
00:04:09,205 --> 00:04:11,845
He just confesses like that?

58
00:04:13,705 --> 00:04:15,605
~ Episode 6 ~

59
00:04:18,595 --> 00:04:21,395
My goodness, what can I say?

60
00:04:21,395 --> 00:04:24,965
He won't make my life difficult at work because I said no, will he?

61
00:04:24,965 --> 00:04:29,165
Why does he like me and yet only make things more complicated?

62
00:04:29,165 --> 00:04:32,055
- Well— - I'll think about it first.

63
00:04:32,055 --> 00:04:33,495
Please?

64
00:04:36,805 --> 00:04:38,325
Please?

65
00:04:39,575 --> 00:04:41,675
It's over there.

66
00:04:43,754 --> 00:04:45,484
Oh no...

67
00:04:45,484 --> 00:04:48,434
He even chose a location for his confession.

68
00:04:50,654 --> 00:04:52,544
Aren't you coming?

69
00:04:54,004 --> 00:04:56,474
I'm coming. I'm coming.

70
00:05:55,802 --> 00:05:58,972
[Yonghan-Quelle]

71
00:05:58,972 --> 00:06:02,882
He wants to make his confession in such a place?

72
00:06:02,882 --> 00:06:05,962
Is this the beautiful place?

73
00:06:05,962 --> 00:06:07,142
Yes.

74
00:06:07,142 --> 00:06:09,572
This is the source that Managing Director An spoke about yesterday.

75
00:06:09,572 --> 00:06:13,592
The water tastes good and is good for a hangover.

76
00:06:14,282 --> 00:06:16,472
[This source has existed since 1392...]

77
00:06:21,712 --> 00:06:23,302
It tastes good.

78
00:06:23,302 --> 00:06:25,332
Did we come here to drink spring water?

79
00:06:25,332 --> 00:06:27,792
Why else would you come here?

80
00:06:31,651 --> 00:06:33,201
Yes.

81
00:06:33,201 --> 00:06:35,351
There's no reason to rush it.

82
00:06:35,351 --> 00:06:36,751
You should try some of it too.

83
00:06:36,751 --> 00:06:39,021
You came from so far away.

84
00:06:42,911 --> 00:06:45,581
I should. I've come this far.

85
00:06:45,581 --> 00:06:47,231
We'll do this together.

86
00:06:47,231 --> 00:06:49,671
Should we raise a glass now?

87
00:07:00,961 --> 00:07:04,121
It cools and refreshes, doesn't it?

88
00:07:04,671 --> 00:07:09,030
Yes, it is very invigorating.

89
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:10,360
Would you like more?

90
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,830
No, I can get it myself—

91
00:07:38,050 --> 00:07:39,660
Nun...

92
00:07:41,970 --> 00:07:43,490
The thing is...

93
00:07:44,189 --> 00:07:45,749
Please?

94
00:07:47,689 --> 00:07:49,069
This is not good.

95
00:07:49,069 --> 00:07:50,049
There...

96
00:07:50,049 --> 00:07:52,769
There's a leaf in the way.

97
00:07:52,769 --> 00:07:53,629
This is not good.

98
00:07:53,629 --> 00:07:56,709
The environment must be perfect for Yongsung's successor.

99
00:07:56,709 --> 00:07:58,369
Let's go now.

100
00:07:59,069 --> 00:08:00,299
Worth...

101
00:08:00,299 --> 00:08:02,019
Was?

102
00:08:03,179 --> 00:08:05,789
Does he think this is a bathroom?

103
00:08:06,639 --> 00:08:09,299
You made the right decision, Chairwoman An.

104
00:08:09,299 --> 00:08:12,309
You said you would think about it, and now here we are.

105
00:08:12,309 --> 00:08:14,269
Thank you for changing your mind.

106
00:08:14,269 --> 00:08:16,489
I will ensure that you receive your winnings.

107
00:08:16,489 --> 00:08:18,189
We do our best to satisfy our customers.

108
00:08:18,189 --> 00:08:20,468
Wonderful. That's fine.

109
00:08:20,468 --> 00:08:23,158
I will speak to the workers first.

110
00:08:23,158 --> 00:08:25,388
and then sign the contract later.

111
00:08:25,388 --> 00:08:29,408
Oh. Of course, you will follow your decision.

112
00:08:29,408 --> 00:08:31,428
On behalf of the Yongsung department store,

113
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:34,488
I will make sure you don't regret your decision.

114
00:08:39,388 --> 00:08:40,878
He's that crazy.

115
00:08:40,878 --> 00:08:42,758
He had a scholarship.

116
00:08:42,758 --> 00:08:45,018
He is so devoted to the company.

117
00:08:45,018 --> 00:08:47,308
Hey, you're acting like a CEO.

118
00:08:47,308 --> 00:08:49,278
Don't be so cheeky.

119
00:08:50,528 --> 00:08:51,858
Frau Baek.

120
00:08:51,858 --> 00:08:53,498
How dare you treat your older brother like that—

121
00:08:53,498 --> 00:08:54,868
Okay, okay, okay.

122
00:08:54,868 --> 00:08:57,717
He is the grandson of the chairwoman of the Yongsun Group.

123
00:08:57,717 --> 00:09:00,117
He is basically the managing director.

124
00:09:07,487 --> 00:09:10,637
I thought you would go to the source yourself instead of asking someone.

125
00:09:10,637 --> 00:09:12,597
Therefore, I have something for you.

126
00:09:12,597 --> 00:09:15,287
I understand that you don't want to disappoint your grandson,

127
00:09:15,287 --> 00:09:17,497
But sometimes you should use your subordinates.

128
00:09:17,497 --> 00:09:19,227
Considering your age

129
00:09:19,227 --> 00:09:21,457
It could hurt your back.

130
00:09:22,097 --> 00:09:23,537
Listen to this.

131
00:09:23,537 --> 00:09:25,827
I return the compliment.

132
00:09:25,827 --> 00:09:29,097
Do you think I'll be impressed by that and sign a contract?

133
00:09:29,097 --> 00:09:30,937
Of course not.

134
00:09:32,496 --> 00:09:35,546
I'm not that naive.

135
00:09:39,716 --> 00:09:41,586
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

136
00:09:41,586 --> 00:09:44,286
I wish you had kept it a secret until the end.

137
00:09:44,286 --> 00:09:45,866
Why are you revealing your identity now?

138
00:09:45,866 --> 00:09:49,206
In order to work together, we need to trust each other.

139
00:09:49,206 --> 00:09:51,276
I'm sorry I didn't tell you this from the beginning.

140
00:09:51,276 --> 00:09:54,396
That's why I wanted you to listen to me.

141
00:09:54,996 --> 00:09:56,916
Chairwoman Jeong...

142
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:59,356
is more concerned about the company than about himself.

143
00:09:59,356 --> 00:10:02,146
She can do anything for Yongsung.

144
00:10:02,146 --> 00:10:06,446
She knows that businesses benefit from a better society.

145
00:10:06,446 --> 00:10:08,585
When her grandson

146
00:10:08,585 --> 00:10:11,545
I am carrying out my grandmother's wishes.

147
00:10:15,345 --> 00:10:17,545
If you sign with us, we will inform you about the foundation

148
00:10:17,545 --> 00:10:19,735
invest in the Ganghan Farm Hospital Foundation

149
00:10:19,735 --> 00:10:23,345
and the construction of the ice factory.

150
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:25,585
Do you mean that seriously?

151
00:10:25,585 --> 00:10:27,075
Yes.

152
00:10:27,885 --> 00:10:32,785
I want these children to one day be as healthy as your grandson.

153
00:10:32,785 --> 00:10:35,045
I mean it.

154
00:10:39,745 --> 00:10:41,525
[Director Ban Ju Yeon]

155
00:10:41,525 --> 00:10:44,744
Did the director say that?

156
00:10:44,744 --> 00:10:48,364
Yes. Like you said, if it has to go to someone else anyway,

157
00:10:48,364 --> 00:10:51,644
It is better if I spend the winnings wisely.

158
00:10:51,644 --> 00:10:55,264
I would be happy if you did all of that.

159
00:10:56,064 --> 00:10:57,844
Yes.

160
00:10:58,454 --> 00:11:01,394
Then we say goodbye.

161
00:11:01,394 --> 00:11:04,454
Okay. Oh right, take that with you.

162
00:11:04,454 --> 00:11:06,364
These are our products

163
00:11:06,364 --> 00:11:10,004
and I also added some Doraji and Godeulbbaegi.

164
00:11:10,004 --> 00:11:12,834
I saw how much you enjoyed it yesterday.

165
00:11:13,584 --> 00:11:15,314
- Take it with you. - Me?

166
00:11:15,314 --> 00:11:17,164
Of course. You both enjoyed it.

167
00:11:17,164 --> 00:11:20,303
Take that too.

168
00:11:27,203 --> 00:11:30,153
It was worth the long trip.

169
00:11:31,283 --> 00:11:34,063
The suggestion you made to the managing director, An...

170
00:11:34,063 --> 00:11:37,343
How long have you been thinking about doing that?

171
00:11:38,273 --> 00:11:41,543
You are the one who made me come up with the idea.

172
00:11:43,763 --> 00:11:46,253
You've let me get this far.

173
00:12:20,192 --> 00:12:21,932
Last night...

174
00:12:21,932 --> 00:12:23,442
And?

175
00:12:25,592 --> 00:12:28,242
So last night...

176
00:12:28,892 --> 00:12:30,662
Last night.

177
00:12:30,662 --> 00:12:32,092
Oh my God!

178
00:12:32,092 --> 00:12:34,621
Will he finally tell me now?

179
00:12:38,231 --> 00:12:41,021
Are you hot? I turned on the air conditioning.

180
00:12:41,021 --> 00:12:43,781
No, it's fine.

181
00:12:49,001 --> 00:12:52,381
I'm ready. Tell me.

182
00:12:52,381 --> 00:12:54,391
Ready for what?

183
00:12:58,301 --> 00:13:02,351
You worked hard yesterday.

184
00:13:06,981 --> 00:13:08,500
Is that all?

185
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:10,490
And if that's okay with you...

186
00:13:10,490 --> 00:13:12,300
What's okay?

187
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:17,110
If that's okay with you, would you like to...?

188
00:13:17,110 --> 00:13:18,980
Listen to my music?

189
00:13:23,150 --> 00:13:25,180
Yes.

190
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:26,890
Of course, go ahead.

191
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:36,290
Play the song I listened to.

192
00:13:37,450 --> 00:13:41,360
I'm playing Crack Shots "Follow Me".

193
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:48,819
♫ Follow! Follow! Follow me! ♫

194
00:14:08,379 --> 00:14:15,199
♫ I've been watching you for quite a while now ♫

195
00:14:15,989 --> 00:14:18,879
♫ It's okay if it's unfamiliar ♫

196
00:14:18,879 --> 00:14:22,948
♫ We surrender ourselves completely to the music ♫

197
00:14:23,788 --> 00:14:28,208
♫ Everything cools down when morning comes ♫

198
00:14:28,208 --> 00:14:31,998
♫ The green light envelops us ♫

199
00:14:31,998 --> 00:14:35,228
When will he speak to me?

200
00:14:35,228 --> 00:14:37,068
♫ Exactly, it's so hot tonight ♫

201
00:14:37,068 --> 00:14:39,868
♫ It's party time! ♫

202
00:14:39,868 --> 00:14:44,468
♫ Follow! Follow! Follow me! ♫

203
00:14:59,687 --> 00:15:02,927
I'll let you go in now.

204
00:15:02,927 --> 00:15:07,187
Are you really just going to drive like that?

205
00:15:09,217 --> 00:15:11,557
I forgot something important.

206
00:15:28,387 --> 00:15:29,457
That's all, right?

207
00:15:29,457 --> 00:15:31,237
Until Monday.

208
00:15:31,237 --> 00:15:34,296
What do you think, is that all?

209
00:15:34,296 --> 00:15:37,406
What happened last night. Will you...

210
00:15:37,406 --> 00:15:39,576
Are you just going to ignore that?

211
00:15:39,576 --> 00:15:43,176
You should explain yourself or something.

212
00:15:43,176 --> 00:15:46,006
That's already in the past. Does it have to be like that?

213
00:15:46,006 --> 00:15:48,616
Let's not make the mistake unnecessarily big.

214
00:15:49,346 --> 00:15:50,426
Mistake?

215
00:15:50,426 --> 00:15:54,946
Yes, a mistake we made while we were drunk.

216
00:15:54,946 --> 00:15:57,556
Wasn't it the same for you?

217
00:16:01,306 --> 00:16:02,576
That was it.

218
00:16:02,576 --> 00:16:04,206
Mistake.

219
00:16:04,886 --> 00:16:06,636
It was a mistake and an accident.

220
00:16:06,636 --> 00:16:09,155
I am not a crazy person.

221
00:16:09,155 --> 00:16:10,415
As you know,

222
00:16:10,415 --> 00:16:14,805
I don't think about you as a man at all.

223
00:16:17,985 --> 00:16:19,535
Why are you suddenly saying something like that?

224
00:16:19,535 --> 00:16:21,415
Did I beg you to see me as a man?

225
00:16:21,415 --> 00:16:24,145
I would have forgiven you if you had begged.

226
00:16:33,215 --> 00:16:34,735
Was?

227
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:40,585
I look masculine.

228
00:16:42,915 --> 00:16:44,645
He's crazy.

229
00:16:44,645 --> 00:16:47,354
Don't make the mistake unnecessarily big?

230
00:16:47,354 --> 00:16:51,004
He kisses girls when he's drunk. He kisses his way through world history.

231
00:17:02,004 --> 00:17:04,764
Why exactly is she angry?

232
00:17:25,193 --> 00:17:27,193
The Makgeolli.

233
00:17:28,123 --> 00:17:30,253
I don't tolerate that well.

234
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:37,443
I fell asleep while waiting for her call.

235
00:17:37,443 --> 00:17:39,603
She left me alone during the night.

236
00:17:41,353 --> 00:17:45,623
Shouldn't I be angry?

237
00:17:59,572 --> 00:18:01,222
Su Jeong.

238
00:18:03,442 --> 00:18:05,302
Su Jeong?

239
00:18:05,302 --> 00:18:07,972
Hi Dad. Did you call me?

240
00:18:07,972 --> 00:18:10,552
You skipped dinner. What were you doing?

241
00:18:10,552 --> 00:18:12,142
The door is stuck.

242
00:18:12,142 --> 00:18:13,572
You don't even use them.

243
00:18:13,572 --> 00:18:15,602
I'm just...

244
00:18:15,602 --> 00:18:18,092
a little sour,

245
00:18:18,092 --> 00:18:21,022
But I can't just smash someone's head in.

246
00:18:22,032 --> 00:18:23,462
Why?

247
00:18:23,462 --> 00:18:25,362
Is it too loud? Should I stop?

248
00:18:25,362 --> 00:18:27,612
No, no. It's okay. Keep going.

249
00:18:27,612 --> 00:18:29,322
Do what you want to do, my love.

250
00:18:29,322 --> 00:18:30,652
Okay.

251
00:19:00,271 --> 00:19:03,131
Yes, I'm the same way.

252
00:19:03,131 --> 00:19:06,361
I was drunk from the alcohol and the mood and I kissed him─

253
00:19:07,561 --> 00:19:10,220
That's no big deal.

254
00:19:10,910 --> 00:19:14,290
It was just the mistake of a single night.

255
00:19:15,010 --> 00:19:16,410
Yes.

256
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:20,770
Mistake?

257
00:19:24,530 --> 00:19:28,450
Shouldn't he apologize if he made a mistake?

258
00:19:53,789 --> 00:19:56,819
- Yes. - How can you sleep now?

259
00:19:58,009 --> 00:19:59,959
Baek Su Jeong?

260
00:20:03,339 --> 00:20:04,709
Did something happen at work?

261
00:20:04,709 --> 00:20:07,309
There's something going on between us.

262
00:20:07,309 --> 00:20:09,749
But I simply can't say what exactly is going on.

263
00:20:09,749 --> 00:20:12,119
What happened yesterday... I mean, the day before yesterday.

264
00:20:12,119 --> 00:20:15,869
Can you simply call it a mistake and move on?

265
00:20:15,869 --> 00:20:17,289
What else should I call it?

266
00:20:17,289 --> 00:20:21,698
I understand. Why are you angry?

267
00:20:21,698 --> 00:20:25,608
- You are understanding? - Yes.

268
00:20:25,668 --> 00:20:29,268
You accidentally drank makgeolli and we spent the night on the farm.

269
00:20:29,268 --> 00:20:31,758
I'm not dwelling on it because it was a mistake.

270
00:20:31,758 --> 00:20:34,288
I am understanding. Quite understanding, in fact.

271
00:20:34,288 --> 00:20:36,468
That's not what I'm talking about at all.

272
00:20:36,468 --> 00:20:38,528
What are you talking about then?

273
00:20:38,528 --> 00:20:40,368
Because you feel bad?

274
00:20:40,368 --> 00:20:41,748
Apologize if you feel bad.

275
00:20:41,748 --> 00:20:43,908
Don't get angry.

276
00:20:43,908 --> 00:20:45,008
Seriously.

277
00:20:45,008 --> 00:20:48,448
Are you telling me I should apologize?

278
00:20:48,448 --> 00:20:49,998
Should I apologize?

279
00:20:49,998 --> 00:20:53,138
You should, since you disappeared while we were drinking together.

280
00:20:53,138 --> 00:20:56,348
How can you leave someone alone who fell asleep while waiting for you?

281
00:20:56,348 --> 00:20:58,407
I was so shocked when I woke up.

282
00:20:58,407 --> 00:21:01,197
I was cold, everything hurt, and the mosquitoes...

283
00:21:01,197 --> 00:21:02,677
It was incredible.

284
00:21:02,677 --> 00:21:04,767
That's why I couldn't sleep well.

285
00:21:04,767 --> 00:21:05,937
Forget it.

286
00:21:05,937 --> 00:21:09,147
I am understanding and will forget about it.

287
00:21:09,757 --> 00:21:12,447
Or did something else happen?

288
00:21:13,347 --> 00:21:15,517
Nothing happened.

289
00:21:27,377 --> 00:21:29,347
Is...

290
00:21:30,097 --> 00:21:32,457
doesn't remember.

291
00:21:46,876 --> 00:21:49,746
He's not a man. He's the same age as Su Bin.

292
00:21:49,746 --> 00:21:52,156
How could I see him as a man?

293
00:21:52,816 --> 00:21:55,116
I remember that she said that back then, too.

294
00:21:55,116 --> 00:21:58,276
And besides, she treated me like a little brother all day.

295
00:22:00,316 --> 00:22:02,026
But why?

296
00:22:04,706 --> 00:22:07,556
Why doesn't she see me as a man?

297
00:22:14,685 --> 00:22:17,245
One million and twenty-one.

298
00:22:17,245 --> 00:22:18,665
She doesn't see me as a man.

299
00:22:18,665 --> 00:22:21,025
One million and twenty-two.

300
00:22:22,035 --> 00:22:25,635
- She doesn't see me... - One million and twenty-three.

301
00:22:28,135 --> 00:22:32,005
She doesn't see me...

302
00:22:33,315 --> 00:22:37,285
They finally reached one million after three years.

303
00:22:37,285 --> 00:22:38,925
They worked very hard.

304
00:22:38,925 --> 00:22:41,315
One million and twenty-four.

305
00:22:41,315 --> 00:22:42,555
We should start counting again from the beginning.

306
00:22:42,555 --> 00:22:44,325
My next goal is two years.

307
00:22:44,325 --> 00:22:46,184
Two years.

308
00:22:50,704 --> 00:22:53,224
She doesn't see me as a man.

309
00:22:55,644 --> 00:22:58,674
- One. - She doesn't see me as a man.

310
00:23:23,753 --> 00:23:26,403
Why doesn't she see me as a man?

311
00:23:26,403 --> 00:23:30,623
Do I need to know what it means to be a man?

312
00:23:39,283 --> 00:23:40,923
Chief Kwon,

313
00:23:40,923 --> 00:23:43,553
You met your husband at your previous job.

314
00:23:43,553 --> 00:23:45,373
He is one year younger than you.

315
00:23:45,373 --> 00:23:48,013
Yes, and then what?

316
00:23:49,723 --> 00:23:52,563
When did you start...

317
00:23:52,563 --> 00:23:54,693
To see him as a man?

318
00:23:58,332 --> 00:24:02,632
Well, he was good at his job and...

319
00:24:03,352 --> 00:24:04,922
I'm already perfect at that.

320
00:24:04,922 --> 00:24:08,052
He spent his money generously on me.

321
00:24:08,052 --> 00:24:10,032
That's too easy.

322
00:24:10,592 --> 00:24:12,612
And that was all?

323
00:24:12,612 --> 00:24:14,102
He was very attentive.

324
00:24:14,102 --> 00:24:18,322
Yes, that was the most important factor.

325
00:24:19,122 --> 00:24:21,492
I already am.

326
00:24:22,512 --> 00:24:25,852
But this is unexpected.

327
00:24:25,852 --> 00:24:31,142
They have never asked me personal questions.

328
00:24:31,142 --> 00:24:34,481
It's the weekend...

329
00:24:34,481 --> 00:24:37,041
Something happened?

330
00:24:39,851 --> 00:24:41,911
That was a professional question.

331
00:24:41,911 --> 00:24:45,941
Knowing them well is part of my job.

332
00:24:45,941 --> 00:24:49,451
In any case, that's what you liked about him.

333
00:24:51,031 --> 00:24:53,071
It's simple.

334
00:25:00,061 --> 00:25:01,941
He was good at his job and...

335
00:25:01,941 --> 00:25:05,081
He spent his money generously on me.

336
00:25:05,081 --> 00:25:06,541
He was very attentive.

337
00:25:06,541 --> 00:25:10,770
Yes, that was the most important factor.

338
00:25:36,550 --> 00:25:39,950
We should all check ourselves in the mirror.

339
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:46,619
[Yongsung Department Store Renewal Information]

340
00:25:57,589 --> 00:26:00,069
It would be a great shame to use this place only as a lounge area.

341
00:26:00,069 --> 00:26:04,679
Could this area play a greater role in attracting new customers?

342
00:26:04,679 --> 00:26:08,389
Yes, it would be a shame not to use this area.

343
00:26:08,389 --> 00:26:12,619
Wow, you have a really good sense for that, Mr. Director.

344
00:26:12,619 --> 00:26:16,569
What do you think, Team Leader Baek?

345
00:26:17,299 --> 00:26:19,059
That sounds like a good idea.

346
00:26:19,059 --> 00:26:20,759
I will consider how the area could be used.

347
00:26:20,759 --> 00:26:22,358
Sounds good.

348
00:26:22,358 --> 00:26:24,598
You haven't had lunch yet, have you?

349
00:26:24,598 --> 00:26:26,108
Please?

350
00:26:27,858 --> 00:26:29,028
Yes.

351
00:26:29,028 --> 00:26:32,298
Then we should go to the Yongsung Hotel next door.

352
00:26:41,718 --> 00:26:44,268
They also got the renovation project on top of everything else.

353
00:26:44,268 --> 00:26:46,178
They all work very hard.

354
00:26:46,178 --> 00:26:49,638
Therefore, I invite you to lunch today.

355
00:26:49,638 --> 00:26:54,828
The pride of the Yongsung Hotel, the S-Class buffet.

356
00:26:56,108 --> 00:26:57,238
Thank you.

357
00:26:57,238 --> 00:26:58,677
Please help yourselves.

358
00:26:58,677 --> 00:27:00,097
Thank you.

359
00:27:00,097 --> 00:27:02,847
Thank you very much.

360
00:27:03,817 --> 00:27:07,787
I also had a lobster dish prepared for each person.

361
00:27:20,717 --> 00:27:23,027
How much will all this cost?

362
00:27:23,027 --> 00:27:24,807
At least 100,000 won per person.

363
00:27:24,807 --> 00:27:27,447
He will indeed be the grandson of the chairwoman.

364
00:27:27,447 --> 00:27:30,727
He treats his chefs as if they were his personal cooks.

365
00:27:30,727 --> 00:27:33,467
Wow, and on top of that, he works so hard?

366
00:27:33,467 --> 00:27:37,096
Oh, I would love to have contact with him.

367
00:27:37,096 --> 00:27:40,496
He will be more popular than Chief Kim from the design team.

368
00:27:40,496 --> 00:27:42,436
I know.

369
00:28:04,306 --> 00:28:06,846
I always thought Director Ban was so unfriendly.

370
00:28:06,846 --> 00:28:08,606
But knows how to do something like that.

371
00:28:08,606 --> 00:28:11,695
He seems to be a workaholic who doesn't date.

372
00:28:11,695 --> 00:28:16,415
Whoever gets it would strike gold. Wouldn't they?

373
00:28:16,415 --> 00:28:18,755
Why are you suddenly telling me this?

374
00:28:18,755 --> 00:28:22,615
They often agree and seem to get along well.

375
00:28:22,615 --> 00:28:26,035
I'm wondering if you want to move up a grade.

376
00:28:26,035 --> 00:28:27,345
I wouldn't have thought you were the right type for that.

377
00:28:27,345 --> 00:28:30,345
Of course, I'm not the type for that.

378
00:28:30,345 --> 00:28:33,035
The director is just a superior to me.

379
00:28:33,035 --> 00:28:37,025
I have never considered him as a friend or husband.

380
00:28:37,715 --> 00:28:40,455
Then you can consider me for that.

381
00:28:43,725 --> 00:28:46,235
She is the strategic team leader.

382
00:28:46,235 --> 00:28:49,284
But you lack creativity.

383
00:28:59,504 --> 00:29:01,134
Bon appetit.

384
00:29:01,134 --> 00:29:02,844
Bon appetit.

385
00:29:02,844 --> 00:29:04,594
Thank you very much, Mr. Director.

386
00:29:05,274 --> 00:29:07,554
Bon appetit.

387
00:29:11,284 --> 00:29:13,394
I lack creativity?

388
00:29:13,394 --> 00:29:16,314
He should be more worried about his memory.

389
00:29:20,294 --> 00:29:22,454
- Yes, Eonni. - Can you talk?

390
00:29:22,454 --> 00:29:24,313
Nothing happened last weekend, did it?

391
00:29:24,313 --> 00:29:26,393
- What? - I was just wondering,

392
00:29:26,393 --> 00:29:29,463
Whether anything happened with your principal on the way home.

393
00:29:30,493 --> 00:29:31,713
Of course not.

394
00:29:31,713 --> 00:29:35,183
Nothing will ever happen with this stupid, shitty wannabe Casanova.

395
00:29:35,183 --> 00:29:37,513
You said he wasn't so bad.

396
00:29:37,513 --> 00:29:39,083
Are you back to normal now?

397
00:29:39,083 --> 00:29:41,383
I added the part about being "stupid and shitty".

398
00:29:41,883 --> 00:29:43,713
What? Is that why you called?

399
00:29:43,713 --> 00:29:45,093
No.

400
00:29:45,093 --> 00:29:47,183
Do you want to go on a blind date?

401
00:29:47,183 --> 00:29:49,613
There's someone who would be a great match for you.

402
00:29:49,613 --> 00:29:51,833
He is older than you and a lawyer.

403
00:29:51,833 --> 00:29:54,013
He is understanding, reliable, and simply adorable.

404
00:29:54,013 --> 00:29:55,433
Totally your type.

405
00:29:55,433 --> 00:29:58,133
You'd better not say no.

406
00:29:58,133 --> 00:29:59,922
Think about it.

407
00:29:59,922 --> 00:30:01,702
Hey!

408
00:30:02,932 --> 00:30:05,522
You! You! You cheeky brat!

409
00:30:05,522 --> 00:30:06,972
You should go on a date instead.

410
00:30:06,972 --> 00:30:08,932
Seriously! Man!

411
00:30:08,932 --> 00:30:10,312
You little...

412
00:30:10,312 --> 00:30:12,472
That hurts! I said I didn't want that.

413
00:30:12,472 --> 00:30:14,372
You are so immature.

414
00:30:14,372 --> 00:30:17,402
That's why you got divorced almost as soon as you got married.

415
00:30:17,892 --> 00:30:21,222
You're the same. Both of you. Seriously...

416
00:30:21,222 --> 00:30:23,142
Why a blind date all of a sudden?

417
00:30:23,142 --> 00:30:24,942
Team leader.

418
00:30:24,942 --> 00:30:26,772
Are you going on a blind date?

419
00:30:26,772 --> 00:30:28,212
Great idea, team leader!

420
00:30:28,212 --> 00:30:29,372
How old is he?

421
00:30:29,372 --> 00:30:30,602
What does he do for a living? Wait a minute.

422
00:30:30,602 --> 00:30:33,102
He can't just have any job to suit you.

423
00:30:33,102 --> 00:30:35,801
Is he good-looking? He's tall, isn't he? How tall is he?

424
00:30:35,801 --> 00:30:38,481
You need to check that without shoes.

425
00:30:38,481 --> 00:30:40,871
I haven't decided yet. I don't know yet.

426
00:30:40,871 --> 00:30:42,541
Who goes on a blind date?

427
00:30:42,541 --> 00:30:44,771
The team leader.

428
00:30:44,771 --> 00:30:46,741
Is that correct?

429
00:30:49,001 --> 00:30:51,911
I asked if that was true.

430
00:30:51,911 --> 00:30:54,311
Why do you want to know that?

431
00:30:54,901 --> 00:30:56,791
K-Don't worry, Mr. Director.

432
00:30:56,791 --> 00:31:00,721
She won't neglect her work just because she's dating.

433
00:31:00,721 --> 00:31:02,961
- Is that right? - Mr. Director.

434
00:31:02,961 --> 00:31:05,541
The chairwoman wants to see you.

435
00:31:05,541 --> 00:31:07,211
Team leader Baek,

436
00:31:07,211 --> 00:31:10,031
Have a quick word with me before you leave for today.

437
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:16,390
He looked happier earlier. How strange.

438
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:28,800
Congratulations.

439
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:33,690
Your life's dream will soon come true.

440
00:31:33,690 --> 00:31:38,160
She asked us to expose you completely to the media.

441
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:41,180
She is trying to make you the official successor.

442
00:31:41,180 --> 00:31:44,660
I thought she was waiting for the results of the contract extension.

443
00:31:44,660 --> 00:31:46,420
It's earlier than I thought.

444
00:31:46,420 --> 00:31:49,729
I think she's planning ahead, since things are going so well.

445
00:31:49,729 --> 00:31:53,019
To be honest, when I gave her the report

446
00:31:53,019 --> 00:31:55,539
She asked about you.

447
00:31:55,539 --> 00:31:57,389
What I thought when I watched you closely.

448
00:31:57,389 --> 00:32:01,369
She asked if you were only focused on work.

449
00:32:04,259 --> 00:32:06,969
Since Yongsung is her life,

450
00:32:06,969 --> 00:32:10,449
She wants her successor to be the same.

451
00:32:11,489 --> 00:32:14,069
What did you say to her?

452
00:32:14,069 --> 00:32:16,139
I told her the truth.

453
00:32:16,139 --> 00:32:19,849
Nobody focuses on their work more than you do.

454
00:32:19,849 --> 00:32:23,318
Just keep doing what you're doing.

455
00:32:23,318 --> 00:32:25,138
In order.

456
00:32:36,248 --> 00:32:41,148
I thought we were similar.

457
00:32:51,728 --> 00:32:54,328
The director is just a boss to me.

458
00:32:54,328 --> 00:32:58,298
I never considered him a friend or husband.

459
00:32:59,757 --> 00:33:02,847
I hope I won't be disappointed.

460
00:33:02,847 --> 00:33:05,227
Just like before.

461
00:33:10,297 --> 00:33:15,577
I wasted my time on silly things.

462
00:33:17,587 --> 00:33:19,987
Wake up, Ban Ju Yeon.

463
00:33:21,067 --> 00:33:23,457
Don't make another mistake.

464
00:33:29,857 --> 00:33:32,497
That's a good summary.

465
00:33:33,147 --> 00:33:34,747
That's it for today.

466
00:33:34,747 --> 00:33:36,966
Thanks.

467
00:33:38,116 --> 00:33:39,846
Aren't you going home, team leader?

468
00:33:39,846 --> 00:33:41,626
I will stop by the director's office first.

469
00:33:41,626 --> 00:33:43,156
Oh?

470
00:33:44,576 --> 00:33:46,796
He's not going to yell at you about the blind date, is he?

471
00:33:46,796 --> 00:33:48,856
Not possible. It must be something else.

472
00:33:48,856 --> 00:33:51,056
Exactly. That doesn't sound right.

473
00:33:51,056 --> 00:33:53,616
Unless he's interested in you. Yes.

474
00:33:53,616 --> 00:33:54,686
Exactly?

475
00:33:54,686 --> 00:33:59,676
Yes. I'm going now.

476
00:33:59,676 --> 00:34:01,306
See you later.

477
00:34:01,306 --> 00:34:02,866
Jun Su!

478
00:34:02,866 --> 00:34:05,026
Jun Su!

479
00:34:05,026 --> 00:34:06,676
Jun Su.

480
00:34:07,326 --> 00:34:10,706
Can I help you with something?

481
00:34:10,706 --> 00:34:12,705
A man...

482
00:34:12,705 --> 00:34:16,775
He visited a woman very late at night to warn her about a womanizer. Why would he do that?

483
00:34:16,775 --> 00:34:17,995
He is interested.

484
00:34:17,995 --> 00:34:20,125
And he gets angry because I don't see him as a man.

485
00:34:20,125 --> 00:34:22,115
- Absolutely - What about kissing while drunk?

486
00:34:22,115 --> 00:34:23,625
And he forgot.

487
00:34:23,625 --> 00:34:27,045
This isn't about you, is it?

488
00:34:27,045 --> 00:34:28,345
No.

489
00:34:28,345 --> 00:34:31,385
I'm talking about a manhwa. A romantic manhwa.

490
00:34:31,385 --> 00:34:33,565
I read it recently.

491
00:34:33,565 --> 00:34:36,725
But I don't understand the psychology of the male lead.

492
00:34:36,725 --> 00:34:40,375
I wonder if you understand them.

493
00:34:40,935 --> 00:34:43,215
Do you also read manhwas? Do we have a pop-up?

494
00:34:43,215 --> 00:34:44,395
Do you think I just work all the time?

495
00:34:44,395 --> 00:34:45,495
Of course not.

496
00:34:45,495 --> 00:34:48,484
Your hobby is personal development. That's why.

497
00:34:48,484 --> 00:34:50,814
Doesn't matter.

498
00:34:53,134 --> 00:34:54,624
By the way,

499
00:34:54,624 --> 00:34:55,784
It's too obvious.

500
00:34:55,784 --> 00:34:58,414
That's a cliché. A cliché.

501
00:34:59,034 --> 00:35:00,444
The fact that they kissed.

502
00:35:00,444 --> 00:35:02,574
He can't have forgotten that.

503
00:35:02,574 --> 00:35:04,994
He's just pretending.

504
00:35:04,994 --> 00:35:07,434
Why is he pretending he forgot?

505
00:35:07,434 --> 00:35:08,804
If he is rejected.

506
00:35:08,804 --> 00:35:12,344
Male leads lack the courage to speak first.

507
00:35:12,344 --> 00:35:14,324
That's just how it is.

508
00:35:14,934 --> 00:35:16,794
You can go home.

509
00:35:16,794 --> 00:35:19,854
Okay. See you later.

510
00:35:27,363 --> 00:35:31,463
No wonder. I knew something was wrong.

511
00:35:32,303 --> 00:35:34,373
I wouldn't have thought he was like that.

512
00:35:34,373 --> 00:35:37,243
But he lacks courage, doesn't he?

513
00:35:43,103 --> 00:35:45,113
Herein.

514
00:35:50,003 --> 00:35:54,533
You wanted to see me before I left.

515
00:35:58,593 --> 00:36:00,162
What's up?

516
00:36:00,162 --> 00:36:03,732
Are you worried because I'm going on a blind date?

517
00:36:03,732 --> 00:36:05,352
Are you trying to stop me from dating?

518
00:36:05,352 --> 00:36:10,352
No. As Deputy Yang said, a relationship won't stop you from working hard.

519
00:36:10,352 --> 00:36:12,212
I'm not worried.

520
00:36:12,212 --> 00:36:15,002
It's none of my business, even as your boss.

521
00:36:17,732 --> 00:36:21,102
You can just be honest.

522
00:36:21,912 --> 00:36:24,652
How could I be even more honest?

523
00:36:24,652 --> 00:36:26,162
Was?

524
00:36:27,942 --> 00:36:29,502
Then...

525
00:36:30,222 --> 00:36:32,832
Why did you come all the way to my house?

526
00:36:32,832 --> 00:36:34,782
You told me not to go out with Chief Kim.

527
00:36:34,782 --> 00:36:37,451
Because you really should watch out for womanizers.

528
00:36:37,451 --> 00:36:39,011
I was just warning you.

529
00:36:39,011 --> 00:36:40,651
Anyone could have stopped you.

530
00:36:40,651 --> 00:36:43,601
I was just being nice. Don't get me wrong.

531
00:36:44,401 --> 00:36:48,391
The chairwoman praised you for signing the contract with Ganghan Farm.

532
00:36:48,391 --> 00:36:50,791
You will soon receive good news regarding your salary negotiation.

533
00:36:50,791 --> 00:36:53,451
You'll also receive a bonus.

534
00:36:53,451 --> 00:36:55,941
That's what I wanted to tell you.

535
00:36:59,971 --> 00:37:01,721
Are you not happy?

536
00:37:01,721 --> 00:37:04,771
You said that money makes you instantly happy.

537
00:37:06,591 --> 00:37:08,671
I am happy.

538
00:37:10,951 --> 00:37:12,850
Thanks.

539
00:37:12,850 --> 00:37:15,120
You can leave.

540
00:37:29,890 --> 00:37:31,870
Was I wrong?

541
00:37:34,660 --> 00:37:37,820
Does that mean I've mixed everything up?

542
00:37:39,530 --> 00:37:40,970
[He kissed for 6,000 won]

543
00:38:03,619 --> 00:38:07,849
